----------------------------------------------------------------------------

                           THE APOCALYPSE 3 RULES

Both the competitors and visitors taking part in the voting are 
automatically bound to agree with these rules. No objections will be heeded
during the comptetition.

Anybody may take part in the compos. The competitor is not required to be 
present at the party - in such a case, the contribution will be delivered
and the possible prize taken over by a respective subtitute (preferred
persons are mentioned in the readme). It's also possible to send your
competition via e-mail to avoid some organizing problems. If you want to
send entriest via e-mail, do it max. 2 days before the party. E-mails will
help us a lot!

All the contributions must be delivered before the deadline (which will be




















announced at the party). No contributions will be accepted after the 
deadline! The contributions may be sent anytime before the party via e- or
snail mail to Lahve/RSN+MWI or Dizzy/HLA.

EACH contribution MUST include a readme file containing the following 
information:
1) name of the production
2) the author
3) the name of the compo you wish to compete in + any other comments which
   should be shown on the screen during the production.
4) the disc should be labelled with the author's name so that we can return
   it to its owner.

If the above mentioned rules are not respected, the author or the production
name may turn out to be missing in the results, as we simply will not have a
chance of knowing this particular information.

The compo contributions must be original, ie. a result of private work. It 
is immoral and unethical to use other people's work!





















The contributions must meet the criteria set for each compo (eg. the size
limit - see the compos limits). In any other case the contribution will be
disqualified.

For the sake of objectivity, the contributions mustn't be released before 
the competition. Releasing means any way of spreading within the public.
If there is any suspicion of a pre-released contribution it will be 
reassigned to the crazy compo or disqualified.

Graphic and music compo contributions can be used in a demo (intro) taking
part in the demo (intro) compo at the same party. The intro and demo compos
will be held as the last ones. Yet it is very inappropriate (although not
forbidden) to use a compo animation screenshot as a 2D compo picture.

All contributions except for the demos and intros will be presented under
handles (not anonymously as a last time).

The voting sheets will be distributed before the compo. Each voter will
receive one sheet that he/she should sign immediately. Votes cast in any
other form are automatically considered invalid.  Please don't swap these




















sheets between each other.

The voter has the right to renounce voting in any competition or for any
(1st, 2nd or 3rd) place in each compo.

Voters are is not allowed to vote for their own contribution(s) or for the
contribution of their own group.

The evalutation will follow a stated system which you will get to know at 
the party.

After the prize ceremony, all contributions will be available for copying
and eventually downloadable on the Internet. Each contributor automatically
gives his/her permission for this by signing up for the competition. If 
there is anybody who does not wish his/her contribution to be treated as a 
shareware product, the organizers are open to any make possible agreement at
the partyplace.

    SMOKING AND THE USE OF NARCOTICS IS STRICTLY PROHIBITED IN THE ROOM!!!!
  Violating this rule may consequently lead to putting the violator out of




















      the room! This ban will be taken care of by selected organizers.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

                     THE APOCALYPSE 3 COMPETITION RULES

ASCII           - One production per artist. No contribution should exceed
                  78x29 characters.

4CH MUSIC       - Four channels. One song per musician. Expect a 3 min. 
                  playtime. File size max. 700 KB. MOD and DBM formats (not
                  required but recommended)

MCH MUSIC       - 5-32 channels. One song per musician. 3 min. playtime.
                  Maximum file size 4MB. MOD, XM, MMD0-3 and DBM (not 
                  required but recommended)

2D GRAPHICS     - Hand-drawn pictures. One picture per graphician. Use of
                  fx. programs  allowed, although not recommended. File size
                  and color depth unlimited. Recommended formats: IFF, GIF, 




















                  PNG (JPG is not recommended due to its lower quality). 
                  Scanned and rendered pictures are not allowed (and will be
                  disqualified)!

TRACE           - Rendered images.        One picture per graphician. Unlimited 
                  file size. Use of someone else`s objects allowed only with
                  an attached .readme file describing the origin of the 
                  object or anything else that comes not originally from the
                  author.

ANIMATION       - Animation without a sound. Playtime max. 6 minutes. Use of
                  someone else`s objects allowed only with an attached 
                  .readme file describing the origin of the object or 
                  anything else that comes not originally from the author.

PRESENTATION    - An animation with a sound track (Scala etc.). Playtime 
                  max. 6 minutes. Use of someone else`s objects allowed only
                  with an attached .readme file describing the origin of the
                  object or anything else that comes not originally from the
                  author.





















64K INTRO       - One production per group. Unlimited playtime. File size 
                  max. 64KB (65536  bytes). AMOS and Demomania products will
                  be reassigned to the Crazy compo.

68K DEMO        - One 68K demo production per group. Playtime is not 
                  limited. AMOS and Demomania products will be reassigned to
                  the Crazy compo.

PPC DEMO        - One PPC demo prod per group. Playtime is not limited. AMOS
                  and Demomania products will be reassigned to the Crazy
                  compo.

CRAZY COMPO     - Completely unlimited productions. Any number of 
                  productions per group.


                         Compo machines available:






















A1260/50 + 32MB RAM, 30GB HDD IDE, 4xEIDE
A1240/35 + PPC 603e+/240, BVisionPPC, E/BOX, 96MB RAM, 6 GB HDD SCSI
A1230/50 + 16MB RAM, 20GB HDD IDE, FastATA


                                  WARNING!

 The rules and limitations have been published in time, thus we call on all
  contributors to strictly observe these rules as ANY CONTRADICTION TO THE
          COMPO LIMITATIONS WILL BE PUNISHED BY DISQUALIFYING!!!!

  The organizers claim the right to change the rules and compo limitations
                 anytime before or during the competition!


ONCE AGAIN WE REMIND YOU TO MAKE SURE TO DELIVER YOUR CONTRIBUTIONS TOGETHER
             WITH THE INEVITABLE README FILES (SEE THE RULES)!!

